Show HN: Crabs All the Way Down – Running Rust on Logic Gates
text:
Made an ARM Thumb CPU from scratch in a digital circuit simulator for fun and decided to push the joke a little further and run real stuff on it, like a Web server, a Scheme interpreter, a MIDI player, and a VT100 emulator.

This is basically a how-did-we-get-here blogpost, it's my second one of this kind, I'd love any feedback you might have.

Show HN: I made a tool to build badges in Pharo
text:
I'd like to share with you a new app for building badges made with Pharo 10 (a fork of Squeak Smalltalk). It is based on the Shields.io badge generation provider.

The idea is to select the badges you want, complete the required variables, and get your badge(s). You can also save and load commonly used variables, so it may help a bit to automate presenting your project's README.

Hernán
